comment_data.body: @DanMossa thanks for this report. Could you follow these steps so I can gather some more information? 1. Uninstall the Flutter plugin (Preferences > Plugins, then click on Flutter) and restart 2. Reinstall the Flutter plugin (same area, can search for Flutter in marketplace) and restart 3. Follow the same steps as you listed to debug your app. 4. Go to the log file in Help > Show log in finder. There should be a file called `idea.log` - attach that here or let me know if you need a private channel to send it.

For anyone having this problem, could you post your operating system and version, and follow the [instructions above](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/5376#issuecomment-815384003) to provide your logs?

I just updated the Flutter plugin in Intellij to v55.1.5 and it seems like the problem is fixed? Anyone else?

> I just updated the Flutter plugin in Intellij to v55.1.5 and it seems like the problem is fixed? Anyone else?

Yes! Thanks for noticing. The problem is not quite fixed, as we are simply not supporting using the embedded browser if it gives an error, but you should stop getting the annoying error messages!

I'm going to keep this issue open because we still want to figure out and fix the cause of the error.
